Theme

Whitecolor="#E69F00"
Chinesecolor="#0072B2"

# theme for boxplots
theme_boxplot<- function () { 
  theme_classic(base_size=10, base_family="Helvetica") +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(size=10, color = "black"),
        axis.text.y = element_text(size=8, color="black"),
        axis.title.x= element_blank(),
        axis.title.y = element_text(size=10, color="black"), 
        legend.position = "none")
}

# theme for pcoas
theme_pcoa<- function () { 
  theme_classic(base_size=10, base_family="Helvetica") +
  theme(axis.text = element_text(size=8, color = "black"), 
        axis.title = element_text(size=10, color="black"), 
        legend.text = element_text(size=8, color = "black"), 
        legend.title = element_text(size=10, color = "black"), 
        plot.title = element_text(size=10, color="black")) +
  theme(panel.border = element_rect(color="black", size=1, fill=NA))
}

PCoA (Bray Curtis)

metaphlan.species %>%
  column_to_rownames("Taxonomy") %>%
  Make.Proportion() -> speciestab

DISTMATRIX<-vegan::vegdist(t(speciestab), method="bray", binary=FALSE, diag=FALSE, upper=FALSE)
PCO<-ape::pcoa(DISTMATRIX)
RESULT<-vegan::adonis(DISTMATRIX ~ Ethnicity, metadata, permutations=999)
print(paste0("-> ADONIS P=", RESULT$aov.tab$`Pr(>F)`[1], " R2=", signif(RESULT$aov.tab$R2[1],3)))
## [1] "-> ADONIS P=0.003 R2=0.0465"
plot_a <- PCO$vectors %>%
  as.data.frame() %>%
  rownames_to_column("SubjectID") %>%
  left_join(metadata) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x=Axis.1, y=Axis.3, fill=Ethnicity)) +
  geom_point(shape=21, size=2) +
  xlab(paste0("PCo1 (", round((100*PCO$values$Eigenvalues/sum(PCO$values$Eigenvalues))[1]), "% Variation Explained)")) +
  ylab(paste0("PCo3 (",round((100*PCO$values$Eigenvalues/sum(PCO$values$Eigenvalues))[3]), "% Variation Explained)")) +
  ggtitle(paste0("p=",RESULT$aov.tab$`Pr(>F)`,", r2=",signif(RESULT$aov.tab$R2[1]),digits=3)) +
  scale_fill_manual(values = c(EA=Chinesecolor, W=Whitecolor)) +
  theme_pcoa()
## Joining, by = "SubjectID"

Compare adonis effect sizes across metadata variables

metadata_adonis<-read_excel("/Volumes/turnbaughlab/qb3share/qiyanang/IDEO_manuscript_Rd2/data/metadata_for_adonis.xlsx") %>% column_to_rownames("SampleID")
adonis_classes<-read_excel("/Volumes/turnbaughlab/qb3share/qiyanang/IDEO_manuscript_Rd2/data/metadata_for_adonis.xlsx",sheet=2)

metadata_adonis <- metadata_adonis %>% rownames_to_column("SampleID")
metadata_adonis2 <- mutate_if(metadata_adonis, is.character, as.factor)

metadata_adonis2 <- 
  metadata_adonis2 %>% 
  separate(SampleID,"SubjectID",extra = "drop") %>% 
  filter(SubjectID %in% colnames(speciestab)) %>% 
  column_to_rownames("SubjectID")


# loop adonis over variables
df_total = data.frame()
for (i in colnames(metadata_adonis2)) {
  form <- as.formula(paste("DISTMATRIX", i, sep="~"))
  adonis_res<- vegan::adonis(form, data=metadata_adonis2, permutations=10000)
  df <- data.frame(Metric=i, Pval=adonis_res$aov.tab$`Pr(>F)`[1], R2=adonis_res$aov.tab$R2[1])
  df_total <- rbind(df_total, df)
}
df_total

shannon diversity using species abundances

alphadiv <- data.frame(
  Shannon = vegan::diversity(metaphlan.species %>% column_to_rownames("Taxonomy"), index = "shannon", MARGIN = 2),
  Richness = vegan::specnumber(metaphlan.species %>% column_to_rownames("Taxonomy"), MARGIN = 2)) %>% 
  rownames_to_column("SampleID") %>% 
  left_join(metadata, by="SampleID") %>% 
  select (SampleID, Ethnicity, Shannon, Richness) %>%
  pivot_longer(cols=Shannon:Richness, names_to="alpha_metric")

# plot alpha div metrics
plot_b <- alphadiv %>%
  filter(!is.na(Ethnicity)) %>% 
  filter(alpha_metric=="Shannon") %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x=Ethnicity, y=value, fill=Ethnicity)) + 
  geom_boxplot(outlier.shape=NA) +
  geom_jitter(shape=21, size=1, height=0, width=0.1) +
  #facet_wrap(~alpha_metric, scales="free", nrow=1) +
  theme_boxplot() +
  scale_fill_manual(values = c(EA=Chinesecolor, W=Whitecolor)) +
  ylab("Shannon diversity") +
  stat_compare_means(label="p.format", method="wilcox.test", paired = FALSE)
plot_b

  filter(Taxonomy %in% phyla) %>%
  pivot_longer(cols=starts_with("OB"), names_to="SubjectID", values_to="pct_abundance") %>%
  left_join(metadata)
## Joining, by = "SubjectID"
plot_c <- metaphlan_phylum %>%
  mutate(Phylum=gsub("k__Bacteria\\|p__","", Taxonomy)) %>% 
  mutate(Phylum=factor(Phylum, levels=c("Firmicutes","Bacteroidetes","Actinobacteria","Proteobacteria","Verrucomicrobia"))) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x=Ethnicity, y=pct_abundance, fill=Ethnicity)) + 
  geom_boxplot(outlier.shape = NULL, outlier.size = -1) +
  geom_jitter(aes(fill=Ethnicity), width = 0.15, shape=21, size=2) + 
  scale_fill_manual(values = c(EA=Chinesecolor, W=Whitecolor)) + 
  facet_wrap(~Phylum, scales = "free", nrow = 1) +
  ggpubr::stat_compare_means(label="p.format",paired=FALSE,method="wilcox.test")+ 
  theme_boxplot() +
  ylab("Relative abundance (%)")
plot_c
